Now we equate the coefficient of the $x^3$ term in our expansion to the coefficient in the original polynomial.

From the expansion: coefficient is $-2(\text{sum of roots})$
From the question: coefficient is $-3$

$$
\begin{aligned}
-2(\text{sum of roots}) &= -3 \\
\text{sum of roots} &= \frac{-3}{-2} \\
\text{sum of roots} &= \frac{3}{2}
\end{aligned}
$$
